The paper proposes a framework for subspace clustering and classification using a low-rank transformation learning approach. This involves learning a linear transformation on subspaces using matrix rank as the optimization criteria. The paper extensively discusses the use of this approach for high-dimensional data such as face images and motion sequences, which suggests that it falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of optimization criteria and learning techniques also suggests that it falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of fast subspace clustering techniques, which suggests that it falls under the data structures (cs.DS) category.
